Function Reference/get boundary post « WordPress Codex
-----------

Get the first or last post by publish date

Usage
-----

` <?php get_boundary_post( $in_same_cat, $excluded_categories, $start ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$in_same_cat` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether post should be in same category.
    Default: false

 `$excluded_categories` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Excluded categories IDs.
    Default: ''

 `$start` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) True to begin at the beginning
    Default: true

Return Values
-------------

-   Post object if successful.
-   Null if global `$post` is not set.
-   Empty string if no corresponding post exists.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

get\_boundary\_post() will set the post pointer to the first post.

Change Log
----------

Since: 2.8.0

Source File
-----------

`get_boundary_post()` is located in `wp-includes/link-template.php`.

